## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability and scope of the sources accessed. The arguments presented are primarily from sources that support the death penalty, which may not fully represent the breadth of the debate. Additionally, the data on deterrence and recidivism is often contested, and the ethical considerations surrounding the death penalty are complex and multifaceted. Further research, including empirical studies and ethical analyses, would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the issue.